{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "48b65815",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# MSM on Prinz potential\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example we study the estimation of a Markov state model based on particles living in the [Prinz potential landscape](../api/generated/deeptime.data.prinz_potential.rst)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "ab14bbd0",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:44.470893Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:43.351833Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "from deeptime.clustering import BoxDiscretization\n",
    "from deeptime.markov import TransitionCountEstimator\n",
    "from deeptime.markov.msm import MaximumLikelihoodMSM\n",
    "from deeptime.data import prinz_potential"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2b0503e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we create the Prinz potential system and generate a plot of its potential function."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "b90fb7ac",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:44.606922Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:44.472921Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "prinz_system = prinz_potential()\n",
    "\n",
    "xs = np.linspace(-1., 1., 500)\n",
    "ys = prinz_system.potential(xs)\n",
    "plt.plot(xs, ys)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('x')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('V(x)');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "98d91dff",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we can simulate trajectories for 50 particles, each starting in the origin $x=0$ and generating 20000 frames."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "e800cd4c",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:54.941048Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:44.608838Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Output shape (50, 20000, 1) for 50 particles, 20000 frames in 1 dimension.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = prinz_system.trajectory(np.zeros((50, 1)), 20000)\n",
    "print(f\"Output shape {data.shape} for {data.shape[0]} particles, {data.shape[1]} frames \"\n",
    "      f\"in {data.shape[2]} dimension.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8c58a1d8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A histogram over the obtained data reflects the (inverse) potential landscape."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "3c6175ef",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.293235Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:54.942981Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.hist(np.concatenate(data), bins=150);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b03d54dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We want to generate a sequence of MSMs under lagtime $\\tau=2$ and varying accuracy regarding the spatial clustering."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "61d869c5",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.298577Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.295049Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lag = 2\n",
    "n_clusters = [5, 7, 10, 15, 30, 50]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "78be13f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Each number of clusters yields a discretization which we use to build a MSM."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "883ec215",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.731635Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.300601Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "clusterings, msms = [], []\n",
    "\n",
    "for n in n_clusters:\n",
    "    cluster = BoxDiscretization(1, n, v0=[-1], v1=[1]).fit_fetch(np.concatenate(data))\n",
    "    clusterings.append(cluster)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    dtrajs = [cluster.transform(x) for x in data]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    count_model = TransitionCountEstimator(lag, 'sliding').fit_fetch(dtrajs)\n",
    "    msm = MaximumLikelihoodMSM().fit_fetch(count_model.submodel_largest())\n",
    "    msms.append(msm)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "91066107",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now look at different properties of the estimated MSMs.\n",
    "\n",
    "The transition matrices from coarse to fine with states ordered from left to right in configuration space:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "a37597e9",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.965833Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.733088Z"
    },
    "tags": [
     "nbsphinx-thumbnail"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x360 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=int(len(msms)//2), figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, msm in zip(axes.flatten(), msms):\n",
    "    ax.imshow(msm.transition_matrix, cmap=plt.cm.Greys)\n",
    "    ax.set_xticks([])\n",
    "    ax.set_yticks([])\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'n = {msm.n_states}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3b12689a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The stationary distribution and first three nontrivial eigenfunctions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "c1e7039b",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:57.646921Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:55.967202Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 24 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_eigenfunctions = 4\n",
    "cmap = plt.cm.Set1\n",
    "\n",
    "f, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=n_eigenfunctions, ncols=len(msms), figsize=(16, 8), sharex=True, sharey=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "finest_cl = clusterings[-1]\n",
    "finest_msm = msms[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "for n, (msm, cluster) in enumerate(zip(msms, clusterings)):\n",
    "    eigenvectors = msm.eigenvectors_left()\n",
    "    for eig_n in range(n_eigenfunctions):\n",
    "        ax = axes[eig_n, n]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        y = eigenvectors.T[:, eig_n]\n",
    "        y = 2*(y-y.min())/(y.max() - y.min()) - 1  # rescale\n",
    "        \n",
    "        y0_ = finest_msm.eigenvectors_left().T[:, eig_n] / finest_msm.eigenvectors_left().T[:, eig_n].max()\n",
    "        y0 = np.interp(cluster.cluster_centers[:, 0], finest_cl.cluster_centers[:, 0], y0_)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if ((-y-y0)**2).sum() < ((y-y0)**2).sum():\n",
    "            y = -y\n",
    "        \n",
    "        ax.step(cluster.cluster_centers[:, 0], y, color=cmap(eig_n), where='mid')\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if n == 0:\n",
    "            lbl = r'$\\mu$' if eig_n == 0 else r'$\\mathrm{{ev}}_{{{}}}$'.format(eig_n)\n",
    "            props = dict(boxstyle='square', facecolor='white', alpha=.8)\n",
    "            ax.text(1., .9, lbl, verticalalignment='top', horizontalalignment='right', \n",
    "                           bbox=props, fontsize='x-small')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "18875879",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And finally, the timescales depending on the coarseness of the MSM."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "3941638c",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:57.977168Z",
     "start_time": "2021-07-20T15:49:57.648774Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x144 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "length = n_eigenfunctions - 1\n",
    "ys = np.arange(length)\n",
    "\n",
    "f, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(8, 2))\n",
    "\n",
    "for n, msm in enumerate(msms):\n",
    "    colors = []\n",
    "    for i in range(length):\n",
    "        colors.append(list(cmap(i+1)))\n",
    "        colors[-1][-1] = ((n+1+len(msms))/(2*len(msms)))\n",
    "    ax.scatter(msm.timescales(k=length), ys, c=colors, marker='s', s=15)\n",
    "ax.semilogx()\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(-.5, 2.5)\n",
    "ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.spines['left'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(.91, 1.99e2)\n",
    "ax.set_yticks([])\n",
    "\n",
    "for n in range(3):\n",
    "    ax.text(0.91, n, r'$\\mathrm{{ev}}_{{{}}}$'.format(n+1), \n",
    "             va='center', ha='left', fontsize='x-small', rotation=90)"
   ]
  }
 ],
